# Render static site routing rules.
# Vite copies this file from public/ to dist/ at build time; Render picks it
# up from the publish directory and applies these rules at its edge.
#
# Rule format: <source>   <destination>   <status>
#   status 200 = rewrite (browser sees the source URL, content from destination)
#   status 301/302 = redirect (browser follows to destination URL)
#
# ORDER MATTERS. First matching rule wins. The API rule must be above the
# SPA fallback, or every /api/* call would get rewritten to index.html.


# ---- API proxy -----------------------------------------------------------
# Reverse-proxy /api/* to the backend web service. The browser only ever
# sees pgpeer.onrender.com, which keeps everything same-origin and lets
# our sameSite='lax' auth cookies flow without CORS gymnastics.
#
# UPDATE the destination if your backend service was named something other
# than 'pgpeer-api' on Render.
/api/*   https://pgpeer-api.onrender.com/api/:splat   200


# ---- SPA fallback --------------------------------------------------------
# Any path that isn't a real file in dist/ (and isn't /api/*, thanks to the
# rule above) serves the React app. Lets React Router handle client-side
# routing for /login, /pgs/:id, /search, etc.
/*       /index.html                                  200